==English==

===Etymology===
From {{Ja.}} {{JAchar|[[アニメ]]}} ''anime'', an abbreviation of {{JAchar|[[アニメーション]]}} ''animēshon'', from English '''[[animation]]'''.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=anime|pl2=animes}}

#{{rfv-sense}} Animated works that originated in [[Japan]].
#*'''2005''', [[w:Joan D. Vinge|Joan D. Vinge]], in ''The Year's Best Fantasy and Horror: Eighteenth Annual Collection'', p. cix
#*:Usually the manga comes first, though it may be an offshoot of a novel, and an '''anime''' may be inspired by a video game.
# An artistic style used in Japanese animation that has also been adopted by some artists in America and other countries.

